Although the United Nations has proclaimed 2011 as [the International Year for
People of African descent](http://portal.unesco.org/culture/en/ev.php-
URL_ID=41031&URL_DO=DO_TOPIC&URL_SECTION=201.html), recently two videos have
been shared through social network that show some cases of racism in Latin
American countries. The first one comes from Chile, where an Ecuadorian
citizen was arrested by the police. They handcuffed him in his hands and feet
just because he crossed the street when the light was red, triggering the
outrage of many people since the very moment that it happened. User[
Tornecino2010](http://www.youtube.com/user/Tomecino2010) uploaded the video to
YouTube.

Most of the YouTube comments condemn what happened:

> pacos [policías] racistas, ojala fueran tan eficientes para atrapar﻿ a los
> lanzas [carteristas] q andan por ahi, en ves de a un hermano inmigrante q
> solo cruza la calle.  
>  [garo1513](http://www.youtube.com/user/garo1513 "garo1513") hace 2 días

Racist cops. I wish they were good enough to get the criminals around here
instead of arresting an immigrant that is just crossing the street.  
